label: idc
comment: Converter DC current, also called Id. It is converter’s state variable, result from power flow.

label: poleLossP
comment:
The active power loss at a DC Pole 
= idleLoss + switchingLoss*|Idc| + resitiveLoss*Idc^2.
For lossless operation Pdc=Pac.
For rectifier operation with losses Pdc=Pac-lossP.
For inverter operation with losses Pdc=Pac+lossP.
It is converter’s state variable used in power flow. The attribute shall be a positive value.

label: uc
comment: Line-to-line converter voltage, the voltage at the AC side of the valve. It is converter’s state variable, result from power flow. The attribute shall be a positive value.

label: udc
comment: Converter voltage at the DC side, also called Ud. It is converter’s state variable, result from power flow. The attribute shall be a positive value.

label: alpha
comment: Firing angle that determines the dc voltage at the converter dc terminal. Typical value between 10 degrees and 18 degrees for a rectifier. It is converter’s state variable, result from power flow. The attribute shall be a positive value.

label: gamma
comment: Extinction angle. It is used to limit the dc voltage at the inverter if needed. Typical value between 17 degrees and 20 degrees for an inverter. It is converter’s state variable, result from power flow. The attribute shall be a positive value.

label: DCTopologicalNodes
comment: The DC topological nodes in a DC topological island.

label: mRID
comment:
Master resource identifier issued by a model authority. The mRID is unique within an exchange context. Global uniqueness is easily achieved by using a UUID, as specified in RFC 4122, for the mRID. The use of UUID is strongly recommended.
For CIMXML data files in RDF syntax conforming to IEC 61970-552, the mRID is mapped to rdf:ID or rdf:about attributes that identify CIM object elements.

label: name
comment: The name is any free human readable and possibly non unique text naming the object.

label: TopologicalNode
comment: The topological node associated with the flow injection state variable.

label: pInjection
comment: The active power mismatch between calculated injection and initial injection.  Positive sign means injection into the TopologicalNode (bus).

label: qInjection
comment: The reactive power mismatch between calculated injection and initial injection.  Positive sign means injection into the TopologicalNode (bus).

label: Terminal
comment: The terminal associated with the power flow state variable.

label: p
comment: The active power flow. Load sign convention is used, i.e. positive sign means flow out from a TopologicalNode (bus) into the conducting equipment.

label: q
comment: The reactive power flow. Load sign convention is used, i.e. positive sign means flow out from a TopologicalNode (bus) into the conducting equipment.

label: ShuntCompensator
comment: The shunt compensator for which the state applies.

label: sections
comment: The number of sections in service as a continuous variable. The attribute shall be a positive value or zero. To get integer value scale with ShuntCompensator.bPerSection.

label: ConductingEquipment
comment: The conducting equipment associated with the status state variable.

label: inService
comment: The in service status as a result of topology processing.  It indicates if the equipment is considered as energized by the power flow. It reflects if the equipment is connected within a solvable island.  It does not necessarily reflect whether or not the island was solved by the power flow.

label: Switch
comment: The switch associated with the switch state.

label: open
comment: The attribute tells if the computed state of the switch is considered open.

label: TapChanger
comment: The tap changer associated with the tap step state.

label: position
comment: The floating point tap position.   This is not the tap ratio, but rather the tap step position as defined by the related tap changer model and normally is constrained to be within the range of minimum and maximum tap positions.

label: TopologicalNode
comment: The topological node associated with the voltage state.

label: angle
comment: The voltage angle of the topological node complex voltage with respect to system reference.

label: v
comment: The voltage magnitude at the topological node. The attribute shall be a positive value.

label: AngleRefTopologicalNode
comment: The angle reference for the island.   Normally there is one TopologicalNode that is selected as the angle reference for each island.   Other reference schemes exist, so the association is typically optional.

label: TopologicalNodes
comment: A topological node belongs to a topological island.

label: delta
comment: Angle between VsConverter.uv and ACDCConverter.uc. It is converter’s state variable used in power flow. The attribute shall be a positive value or zero.

label: uv
comment: Line-to-line voltage on the valve side of the converter transformer. It is converter’s state variable, result from power flow. The attribute shall be a positive value.
